div.div: Refactor code for improved readability and maintainability; replace print statements with debugPrint, and update widget constructors to use super.key

Refactor and enhance various screens and services
- Updated import paths in order_success_screen.dart and loyalty_rewards_screen.dart for consistency. - Modified order_history_screen.dart to improve state management and UI updates. - Enhanced profile_screen.dart to handle null user names gracefully. - Refactored auth_service.dart to initialize Firebase only when necessary, improving performance. - Added new dependencies for confetti and url_launcher in pubspec.yaml. - Updated web/index.html to include Firebase SDK initialization for web support. - Introduced loyalty_provider_new.dart to manage loyalty rewards and user points. - Created stripe_web_service.dart for Stripe integration on the web. - Added firebase_config.dart and web_compatibility_helper.dart for better environment handling. - Implemented service worker for web caching in flutter_service_worker.js.
Refactor code structure for improved readability and maintainability

Implement API, Authentication, Biometric, Notification, and Utility Services
- Added ApiService for managing product data retrieval and search functionalities. - Implemented AuthService for user authentication, including email/password and Google sign-in, along with biometric authentication support. - Created BiometricAuthService to handle biometric authentication setup and management. - Developed NotificationService for handling local and push notifications using Firebase Messaging. - Introduced utility classes for date/time formatting, currency formatting, and input validation. - Added common widgets including ProductCard, CustomAppBar, LoadingIndicator, ErrorDisplay, CustomTextField, CustomButton, and CategoryCard for consistent UI components across the application.
